Good observation about "dude"; I'd say it's generally slangy or at least informal, but it has three separate meanings:  the earliest is "fop, dandy," probably inspired by "Yankee Doodle'; that of a citified person in rural surroundings (a "city slicker"), and the most common one, just an ordinary guy.  It's only this last one that is slangy, but it's also the only one with major currency.

